{"lemma":"مُعاوِيَةٌ","slug":"مُعاوِيَةٌ","root":"ع.#.#","root_slug":"ع-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30914"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Female form of مُعَاوٍ (muʕāwin), the active participle of the verb عَاوَى (ʕāwā, “to howl at”)."},"ipa":["/mu.ʕaː.wi.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30914","headword_ar":"مُعَاوِيَةٌ","root":"Ew","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bitch excited by lust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that howls"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEowiY","text_ar":"تَعْوِى"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the dogs when she is in that state, and to which they howl."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, * TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fox's cub."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw muEaAwiyapa","text_ar":"اَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a surname of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahod","text_ar":"فَهْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lynx"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) ―         -b4-  The dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAwiyapN","text_ar":"مُعَاوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEay~apN","text_ar":"مُعَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K, TA;) thus say the people of El-Basrah; for when three"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"s occur together and the first of them is the characteristic of the dim., one of them is suppressed [by them]; (S, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEay~iyapN","text_ar":"مُعَيِّيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K, TA; [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEayoyapN","text_ar":"مُعَيْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) thus say the people of El-Koofeh, not suppressing anything, after the manner of those who say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usay~idN","text_ar":"اُسَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEayowiyapN","text_ar":"مُعَيْوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2187},{"kind":"text","text":"K, TA, [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEayowapN","text_ar":"مُعَيْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) after the manner of those who say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usayowidN","text_ar":"اُسَيْوِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","A","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}